# Language & Content Conventions

## Language Usage Rules

- **Vietnamese**: All user-facing text, UI labels, messages, and business content
- **English**: Code, comments, documentation, variable names, and technical terms
- **Mixed Context**: Business domain terms may use Vietnamese in UI but English in code

## UI Text Standards

- Page titles, button labels, form fields → Vietnamese
- Error messages and user feedback → Vietnamese
- Navigation menus and breadcrumbs → Vietnamese
- Business terms: "Nhân viên", "Đơn hàng", "Bàn ăn", "Món ăn", "Phân tích"

## Code Standards

- Variable names, function names, comments → English
- TypeScript interfaces and types → English
- API endpoint names and schema → English
- File names and directory names → English

## Examples

### Good UI Text (Vietnamese)

```typescript
// In components
<Button>Thêm nhân viên</Button>
<h1>Quản lý đơn hàng</h1>
<Label>Tên đăng nhập</Label>
<p>Đã cập nhật thông tin thành công</p>
```

### Good Code (English)

```typescript
// Variables and functions
const employeeList = data?.payload.data
const handleSubmitForm = () => {}
const useAccountMe = () => {}

// Types and interfaces
interface EmployeeFormData {
  name: string
  email: string
}

// Comments
// Handle form submission and update employee data
// TODO: Add validation for email format
```

